    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early 19th-century American rugs woven in broad lengthwise stripes with a heavy homespun wool yarn, the width was suitable for stair coverings or they were seamed together to make room-sized rugs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
